WEBVTT

00:00:00.830 --> 00:00:05.251
The world has lost 68 percent
of its wildlife populations

00:00:05.251 --> 00:00:06.836
in under 50 years,

00:00:06.878 --> 00:00:08.671
and there are people around the world

00:00:08.671 --> 00:00:11.924
working to protect and grow
the wildlife that is left.

00:00:12.967 --> 00:00:14.635
In Africa, however,

00:00:14.677 --> 00:00:16.596
the approach to conserving this wildlife

00:00:16.596 --> 00:00:20.975
has almost always involved
a separation of people from nature,

00:00:21.017 --> 00:00:24.604
the involvement, but never
leadership, from local people,

00:00:24.645 --> 00:00:28.733
and a problem statement that has often
come from outside our continent.

